{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, CustomerSheet will accept all supported cards by Stripe."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can specify card brands CustomerSheet should block disallow or allow payment for by providing an array of those card brands."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: For Apple Pay, the list of supported card brands is determined by combining "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StripeAPI.supportedPKPaymentNetworks()"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StripeAPI.additionalEnabledApplePayNetworks"},{"type":"text","text":" and then applying the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cardBrandAcceptance"},{"type":"text","text":" filter. This filtered list is then assigned to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKPaymentRequest.supportedNetworks"},{"type":"text","text":", ensuring that only the allowed card brands are available for Apple Pay transactions. Any "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PKPaymentNetwork"},{"type":"text","text":" that does not correspond to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BrandCategory"},{"type":"text","text":" will be blocked if you have specified an allow list, or will not be blocked if you have specified a disallow list."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: This is only a client-side solution."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Note: Card brand filtering is not currently supported by Link."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/stripepaymentsheet\/customersheet\/configuration\/cardbrandacceptance"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:18StripePaymentSheet08CustomerC0C13ConfigurationV19cardBrandAcceptanceAA0bC0C04CardgH0Ovp","modules":[{"name":"StripePaymentSheet"}],"symbolKind":"property","title":"cardBrandAcceptance","roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cardBrandAcceptance","kind":"ide